# Supabase Layer

Read `docs/DATABASE.md` and `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.

## Client

Import from `@/lib/supabase` — singleton, never create new clients.

## File Split

| Reads | Writes |
|-------|--------|
| `<domain>.service.ts` | `<domain>.mutations.ts` |
| No `"use server"` | `"use server"` required |
| `get*`, `list*`, counts | `create*`, `update*`, `delete*` |

## Tables in Use

- `rooms` — id, hotel_id, room_type, capacity, price
- `bookings` — guest fields, dates, total_price, status, room_id
- `guests` — name, contact, total_bookings, total_spent
- `leads` / `hotel_leads` — AI inquiry pipeline

## RPC

- `list_hotel_leads(p_hotel_id, p_limit)` — fetch leads
- `update_lead_status(p_lead_id, p_status)` — lead workflow

## Mutation Pattern

```typescript
"use server";
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";
import { supabase } from "@/lib/supabase";

export async function createX(input: CreateXInput) {
  const { error } = await supabase.from("table").insert({ ... });
  if (error) throw error;
  revalidatePath("/route");
}
```

## Business Rules (in mutations)

- `ensureRoomAvailable()` — reject overlapping bookings
- `calculateTotalPrice()` — room.price × nights (min 1)

## Tenant

Always include `hotel_id`. Current: `"hotel_aurora"`. Filter all queries by tenant.

## Errors

- Mutations: `throw error` or `throw new Error("Russian message")`
- New services: throw on read failure (don't silently return `[]`)
